				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Will post things here that I think would be useful for others to know.
<br />

<br />
One thing I have observed is that when a Sleeping Mob wakes, he will sometimes simply forget about his aggro if you are out of his aggro range or in a stealth mode.
<br />

<br />
Teleport Foe will wake a mob's friends, so you can't Mass Hypnotize em and then try to TP one out without waking all his sleeping friends.
<br />

<br />
Some Bosses and Lts have something weird going-on regarding Sleep.  I can cast Hold on them and do damage or punch them just fine for the duration of the Hold...but, if I cast any type of Sleep while it is Held, it seems to overwrite the Hold and they immediately wake-up.  This only seems to happen with some of the Bosses because I can Hold/Sleep most other mobs with no problem.
<br />

<br />
Storm Summoning Ability of Snow Storm does an AOE Slow/Reduce Movement ... this is PBAOE around the target so any new mobs that get close are also slowed.  Best to kill this mob last if at all possible and to train any new mobs close enough to it to get slowed as well ... once slowed a mob will remain slowed till either original target is dead or the ability is shut-off.
<br />

<br />
Sleeping Mobs appear a bit hunched over and have Zzz's floating above their head.<br />_________________<br />Major Rosha
<br />
Mutant Oriented Tank
<br />
Invul/Energy
<br />
