			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Boss Mobs have high resists to Sleeps, Holds and Disorients, they also tend to break early from these if you do happen to land one.
<br />

<br />
Sleeps and Holds are at the same Debuff Stacking level.  If you cast a sleep on a held mob, it overwrites the hold and converts it to a sleep.  This is generally a bad thing as you can not damage a sleeping mob or you break sleep.   Sleep does last about twice as long as a Hold.   But Holds are far more useful as you can pummel held mobs without breaking the hold.
<br />

<br />
Deceive and Confuse are invaluable tools for Crowd control.  Their attack rating is at +20%.   So you can fairly reliably land a charm power on an orange or even purple mob.  Charms have a range of 80.  So are at full nuke range.  Cause ZERO agro, even on a miss and even when the mob breaks charm.  Their best use is to lock down an Orange Lieutenant in a pack of mobs.   You can nuke, sleep or hold a charmed mob and it does not break the charm.  Once you have all the mobs locked down, it is generally a good idea to root/hold your charmed mobs to prevent them from KS-ing or running off.  Consider Charm powers as a LURE type Hold/Disorient, and not as a charm solo-ing power, as charmed damage subtracts from your experience.  You can sit back at max range 80 and cast charm as many times as it takes to land it on a high con Lieutenant without agroing.  It has a recast around 8 seconds and lasts around 30 seconds, so you can potentially have three mobs charmed for around 6 seconds when the first will break.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
